    <id>https://www.nber.org/papers/w34702</id>
    <title>Kalshi and the Rise of Macro Markets</title>
    <updated>2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Anthony M. Diercks, Jared Dean Katz &amp; Jonathan H. Wright</name>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;b&gt; NBER Working Papers&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;Prediction markets offer a new market-based approach to measuring macroeconomic expectations in real-time. We evaluate the accuracy of prediction market-implied forecasts from Kalshi, the largest federally regulated prediction market overseen by the CFTC. We compare Kalshi with more traditional survey and market-implied forecasts, examine how expectations respond to macroeconomic and financial news, and how policy signals are interpreted by market participants. Our results suggest that Kalshi markets provide a high-frequency, continuously updated, distributionally rich benchmark that is valuable to both researchers and policymakers.</content>
